            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I like it.  I can be specific "
              },
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "UJFN50C00"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ".  Godek's key point is about having principled rather than ad-hoc representations.  What does that mean?  One way to say it is that wiggle in the representation should correspond to an underlying wobble.  Programming language text as interpreted by parsers and compilers generally doesn't work this way because small changes in the text generally correspond to errors."
              }
            ]
          }
